# thoth_endpoint

Registers and updates a Thoth endpoint record.

Use this resource when you want Terraform-managed endpoint IDs and agent
bindings, for example to drive endpoint-scoped and agent-scoped API key tests.

## Example Usage

```terraform
resource "thoth_fleet" "dev" {
  name   = "trantor-dev"
  region = "us-west-2"
}

resource "thoth_endpoint" "coding_workstation" {
  endpoint_id      = "trantor-dev-endpoint-01"
  hostname         = "coding-workstation-01.cawlo.dev"
  environment      = "dev"
  status           = "online"
  enforcement_mode = "shadow"
  fleet_id         = thoth_fleet.dev.fleet_id
  provider_name    = "terraform"
  agent_ids        = ["coding-agent"]
}
```
